<p class="ie7"><strong>Admission to BYU-Idaho for new freshmen is based 40% on academic factors. These factors include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cumulative un-weighted high school grade point average (GPA)</li>
<li>ACT or SAT scores</li>
<li>AP or IB classes</li>
<li><a class="intLink" href="x18617.xml">GED or COMPASS</a> scores (*required of students from home, private, charter school, and non-nationally accredited public school programs in place of the high school GPA)</li>
</ul>
<h3><img alt="Admission Requirements Graphic" height="323" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Admissions/AdmissionRequirements_Image_710(1).jpg" title="Admission Requirements Graphic" width="710" /></h3>
<p><strong>Testing Requirements and Academic Minimums</strong></p>
<p>New freshmen and transfer students with less than 24 credits completed by the application deadline must take the ACT or SAT.</p>
<p>Since students often improve after taking the ACT or SAT a second time, we encourage students to test more than once. Mid-junior year of high school is a good time to begin testing. To learn more about the ACT or SAT tests or to sign up, please visit <a href="http://www.act.org/">www.act.org</a> or <a href="http://www.sat.org/">www.sat.org</a>. BYU-Idaho will use the highest score submitted prior to the application deadline.</p>
<p><strong>New Freshmen &amp; Transfer Students with Less Than 24 Completed Semester (36 quarter hours) Credits</strong></p>
